@node 007 Armenia
Nature and climate: High Armenian Plateau with mountains; little forest
   land; fast flowing rivers; good soil in Aras River valley. The climate
   is continental, hot and sobject to drought.
Natural resources: Small deposits of gold, copper, molybdenum, zinc and
   alumina.
People: Armenian 93%, Azeri 3%, Russian 2% and other 2%.
Independence: 23 September 1991 from Soviet Union.
@endnode
@node 197 Aruba
Nature and climate: Flat with a few hills and scant vegetation. Tropical
   marine climate with little seasonal temperature variation.
Natural resources: White sandy beaches.
People: Mixed European/Caribbean Indian 80%
Independence: None (part of Dutch realm).
@endnode
