@node 016 Benin
Nature and climate: Mostly flat to undulating plain and some hills and low
   mountains. Hot, humid climate in south and semiarid in north.
Natural resources: Oil, limestone, marble and timber.
People: African 99%, Europeans 5 500.
Independence: 1 August 1960 from France.
@endnode
@node 198 "Bermuda Islands"
