@node 026 Burundi
Nature and climate: Mostly rolling to hilly highland. Warm, temperate
   climate, with occasional frost in uplands.
Natural resources: Nickel, uranium, rar earth oxide, peat, cobalt, copper,
   platinum and vanadium.
People: Hutu 85%, Tutsi 14% and Twa 1%.
Independence: 1 July 1962 from UN trusteeship under Belgian administration.
