@node 076 Cameroon
Nature and climate: Diverse, with coastal plain in soutwest, dissected
   plateau in center, mountains in west and plains in north. Climate varies
   with terrain from tropical along coast to semiarid and hot in north.
Natural resources: Petroleum, bauxite, iron ore, timber and hydropower
   potential.
People: Cameroon Higlanders 31%, Equatorial Bantu 19%, Kirdi 11%, Fulani
   10%, Northwestern Bantu 8%, Eastern Nigritic 7%, other African 13% and
   non-African less than 1%.
Independence: 1 January 1960 from UN trusteeship under French administration.
History: From 1884 to 1916 the territory was a German protectorate; it was
   then administered under League of Nations, Later UN, rusteeship, part by
   France and by part by Britain. In 1960 French Cameroon became an
   independent republic, to be joined in 1961 by part of the British
   Cameroons; the remainder became part of Nigeria. The French and British
   halves of the territory at first had separate governments but in 1972
   merged as a United Republic.
@endnode
