@node 028 "Central African Republic"
Nature and climate: Vast, flat to rolling and scattered hills in northeast
   and southwest. Tropical climate with hot, dry winters and mold to hot,
   wet summers.
Natural resources: Diamonds, uranium, timber, gold and oil.
People: Baya 34%, Banda 27%, Sara 10%, Mandjia 21%, Mboum 4% and M'Baka 4%.
Independence: 13 August 1960 from France.
