@node 062 Honduras
Nature and climate: Mostly mountains in interior and narrow coastal plains.
   Subtropical climate in lowlands and temerate in mountains.
Natural resources: Timber, gold, copper, lead, zinc, iron ore, antimony,
   coal and fish.
People: Mestizo 90%, Indian 7%, black 2%, white 1%.
Independence: 15 September 1821 from Spain.
History: Discovered by Columbus in 1502, for nearly three centuries until 
   the proclamation of independence in 1821 Honduras was a dependency of 
   Spain.
