@node 117 Nicaragua
Nature and climate: Extencive Atlantic coastal plains rising to central
   interior mountains; narrow Pacific coastal plain interrupted by
   volcanoes. Tropicla climate in lowlands and cooler in inland.
Natural resources: Gold, silver, copper, tungsten, lead, zinc, timber and
   fish.
People: Mestizo 69%, white 17%, black 9%, Indian 5%.
Independence: 15 September 1821 from Spain.
History: Columbus sighted the eastern coast in 1502, and the country was
   colonized by the Spaniards in the early 16th century. It broke away in
   1821, and after breif membership of the Central American Federation
   became an independent republic in 1838. Since then its history has been
   scarred by border disputes and internal disturbances, the last witnessing
   the successful overtrow of the dictator Anastasio Somoza in 1979,
   followed by a continuing counter-revolutionary campaign against the new
   left-wing Sandinista regime.
