@node 136 Russia
Nature and climate: Broad plain with low hills west of Urals, vast
   coniferous forest and tundra in Siberia, and uplands and mountains along
   southern border regions. Humid continental climate in much of European
   Russia and subarctic in Sibira to tundra climate in the polar north.
Natural resources: Wide natural resources base including majo deposits of
   oil, natural gas, coal, and many strategic minerals, timber.
People: Russian 81.5%, Tatar 3.8%, Ukrainian 3%, Chuvash 1.2%, Bashkir 0.9%,
   Belarusian 0.8%, Moldavian 0.7%, other 8.1%.
Independence: 24 August 1991 from Soviet Union.
@endnode
