@node 153 "Spain"
Nature and climate: Large flat to dissected plateau surrounded by rugged
   hills and Pyrenees in north. Temperate climate with clear, hot summers in
   interior (more moderate and cloudy along coast) and cloudy, cold winters
   (partly cloudy and cool along coast).
Natural resources: Coal, lignite, iron ore, uranium, mercury, pyrites,
   fluorspar, gypsum, zinc, lead, tungsten, copper, kaolin, potash and
   hydropower.
People: Composite of Mediterranean and Nordic types.
Independence: 1492.
History: Conquered successively by the Carthaginians, Romans, Visigoths and 
   Arabs, Spain was reunited by the marrige of Ferdinand of Aragon and 
   Isabella of Castile at the end of the 15th centuryand emerged under the 
   Hapsburg kings of the 16th century to become the dominant European power. 
   Thereafter it declined, suffering as a result of the War of the Spanish 
   Succession and the Napoleonic War, and losing most of its overseas empire 
   in the early 19th century. Endemic political instability finally resulted 
   in the Spanish Civil War (1936-9) and the establishment of a Fascist 
   dictatorship under Franco. Franco's death in 1975 was followed by the 
   re-establishment of a constitutional monarchy and a pronounced 
   liberalization of the State.
@endnode
