@node 186 Vietnam
Nature and climate: Low, flat delta in south and north, central highlands,
   and mountainous in far north and northwest. Tropical climate in south,
   and monsoonal climate in north with rainy season (mid-May to
   mid-September) and dry season (mid-October to mid-March).
Natural resources: Phosphates, coal, manganese, bauxite, chromate, offshore
   oil deposits, and forests.
People: Vietnamese 85-90%, Chinese 3%, Muong, Thai, Meo, Khmer, Man and Cham
   9-7%.
Independence: 2 September 1945 from France.
